<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Yoohoo</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-03 05:04:10</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The main problem in getting these (at least as a solo) is that the batons are so loved by everyone that these are always camped--usually by a full group, but if not that, but a single 50-ish character clearing everything so he gets a chance at the lumpys.<BR>
<BR>
I've camped Dalnir's non-stop pretty much for about 70 hours (long enough to get a robe of foci, sarnak ceremonial dagger, maybe 8 bamboo bo sticks, etc) but only today got a chance at a lumpy that wasn't camped.  I'm high enough to just steal it from people, but didn't want to do that (45 druid).  Normally I've been camping imprecator and crusader.<BR>
<BR>
These items are so desired that I wouldn't sell mine for the 1100 some people are talking about.  Not even having one before, I saw many people advertising 1500 for them.  By comparison, I have not been able to sell even a single bamboo bo stick, even though it's faster than a gnoll hide lariat and does almost 3 times the damage (no stun though) yet it's a 2hb!! Every monk is going 1hb now, and fighting batons are IT.  Get 20 if you can, and don't sell them cheap.  People are crazy for this weapon now.<BR>
<BR>
And bizarrely and tragically, the place where it drops often has no monks, though it is fully of a massive variety of no-drop good monk stuff.  Get your monk to Dalnir's and don't leave if you can avoid it!<BR>
<BR>
P.S. Druids have the strongest anti-summoned spells in the game, and most mobs here are summoned! All the "coerced" besides iksars and goblins die very very quick to anti-summoned spells compared to regular blasts.  Druids and monks, you need no other zone.  Druids maybe lava or steamfont, but...well...nah.  Drops much better here.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
